15/02/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Foreign Minister Solomon Passy and his Romanian counterpart, Mircea Geoana, met on Saturday (14 February), pledging the two countries' willingness to see each other successfully complete accession talks with the EU.
They agreed they must now focus on the financial framework recently released by the European Commission.
They are to join the EU in 2007.
In other news, Lieutenant Colonel Nasko Ljutskanov, commander of the second Bulgarian battalion in Iraq, is being replaced because he cannot speak fluent English.
His replacement will be announced Tuesday, according to the defence ministry.
(bTV, BTA, BNT, Nova TV - 14/02/04)
